<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8" />
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0" />
  <title>Signals in the Noise</title>
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="../style.css" />
</head>
<body>
  <main class="post-shell">
    <a class="back-link" href="../index.html">← Back to Blog Archive</a>

    <article class="pixel-panel" aria-labelledby="post-title">
      <h1 id="post-title">Signals in the Noise</h1>
      <p class="small-muted">March 15, 2026</p>

      <section aria-label="Tags">
        <strong>Tags:</strong>
        <div class="tags">
          <span class="tag">obligatory highpost</span>
          <span class="tag">therapy</span>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section class="post-content" aria-label="Main content">
        <p>
          The room had that electric hush again—the one that arrives after midnight,
          when every little sound feels like a transmission from somewhere else.
        </p>
        <p>
          I wrote this down to remember the feeling: static is not always interference.
          Sometimes it is evidence that the line is still alive.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="permalink-row" aria-label="Permalink">
        <strong>Permalink:</strong>
        <span id="permalinkText"></span>
        <button type="button" class="copy-btn" id="copyPermalinkBtn">Copy Permalink</button>
        <span id="copyStatus" class="small-muted" aria-live="polite"></span>
      </section>
    </article>
  </main>

  <script>
    const permalinkText = document.getElementById("permalinkText");
    const copyBtn = document.getElementById("copyPermalinkBtn");
    const copyStatus = document.getElementById("copyStatus");

    const fullUrl = window.location.href;
    permalinkText.textContent = fullUrl;

    copyBtn.addEventListener("click", async () => {
      copyStatus.textContent = "";
      try {
        await navigator.clipboard.writeText(fullUrl);
        copyStatus.textContent = "Copied!";
      } catch (_) {
        copyStatus.textContent = "Copy failed. You can manually copy the URL above.";
      }
    });
  </script>
</body>
</html>
